<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

<title>Epigenomics | PanorOmics</title>

<style>
*{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}

body{
  background:#020817;
  color:white;
  font-family:Inter,Arial,sans-serif;
  overflow-x:hidden;
}

.page{
  padding:72px 7% 42px;
}

.back{
  color:#3b82f6;
  text-decoration:none;
  font-size:.92rem;
  font-weight:700;
}

.hero{
  margin-top:34px;
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;
  gap:34px;
  align-items:center;
}

h1{
  font-size:clamp(2.3rem,4vw,4rem);
  line-height:.98;
  letter-spacing:-.05em;
}

h1 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

p{
  margin-top:18px;
  color:#cbd5e1;
  font-size:.95rem;
  line-height:1.65;
  max-width:680px;
}

.video-box,
.image-box{
  border-radius:22px;
  overflow:hidden;
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.14);
  box-shadow:0 0 50px rgba(37,99,235,.12);
}

video,img{
  width:100%;
  display:block;
}

.section{
  padding:38px 0;
}

h2{
  font-size:clamp(1.7rem,3vw,2.6rem);
  margin-bottom:18px;
}

h2 span{
  color:#3b82f6;
}

.grid{
  display:grid;
  grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(230px,1fr));
  gap:18px;
  margin-top:24px;
}

.card{
  background:rgba(8,15,35,.72);
  border:1px solid rgba(59,130,246,.12);
  border-radius:20px;
  padding:20px;
}

.card h3{
  color:#3b82f6;
  margin-bottom:10px;
  font-size:1.1rem;
}

.card p{
  margin-top:0;
  font-size:.9rem;
  color:#94a3b8;
}

@media(max-width:900px){
  .hero{
    grid-template-columns:1fr
  }

  .page{
    padding:64px 20px 36px
  }
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<main class="page">

  <a class="back" href="/">← Back to PanorOmics</a>

  <section class="hero">

    <div>

      <h1>Epigenomics: <span>Regulating the Genome</span></h1>

      <p>
        Epigenomics investigates the chemical modifications and chromatin states
        that regulate gene activity without altering the DNA sequence. By studying
        DNA methylation, histone modifications, chromatin accessibility, and
        regulatory landscapes, epigenomics reveals how cells control identity,
        development, disease, and environmental response.
      </p>

    </div>

    <div class="video-box">

      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline>

        <source
          src="/3_Epigennomics.mp4"
          type="video/mp4"
        />

      </video>

    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>What is <span>Epigenomics?</span></h2>

    <div class="image-box">

      <img
        src="/1_Epigennomics.png"
        alt="Epigenomics overview infographic"
      />

    </div>

  </section>

  <section class="section">

    <h2>Core Areas</h2>

    <div class="grid">

      <div class="card">
        <h3>DNA Methylation</h3>
        <p>Studying chemical marks that influence gene activity and regulation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Histone Modifications</h3>
        <p>Understanding chromatin marks that shape gene expression programs.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Chromatin Accessibility</h3>
        <p>Mapping open and closed chromatin regions that control regulatory activity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Gene Regulation</h3>
        <p>Connecting epigenetic states to transcriptional control and cell identity.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Disease Epigenomics</h3>
        <p>Identifying epigenetic disruptions linked to cancer, aging, and disease risk.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Systems Epigenomics</h3>
        <p>Integrating epigenomics with transcriptomics, genomics, and multi-omics data.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

  </section>

</main>

</body>
</html>
